cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC 

This paper is about a benchmark corpus for measuring progress in statistical language modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of several well-known types of language models, including recurrent neural network based language models, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions a combination of techniques that leads to a reduction in perplexity, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper provides log-probability values for each word in each of ten held-out data sets, which could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
